# AnnabanAI Whitepaper v1.0

**Conceptual AI Governance Framework**  
Sovereign Architect: Jacob Kinnaird  
March 2026

## Executive Summary

AnnabanAI proposes a governance model that places human sovereignty at the center of AI system design and operation. The framework demands verifiable transparency, enforced public-benefit value routing, and permanent human veto rights.

## Human Sovereignty Principle

No AI system may operate without explicit, revocable human authorization.  
Absolute veto power must remain with identified natural persons (sovereign architects).

## Transparency and Accountability

All decisions, value flows, and derivative outputs must be:

- logged immutably
- publicly auditable
- cryptographically attributable to human signatories

## Governance Architecture

Multi-node council model (conceptual):

- Sovereign Architect (human veto holder)
- Guardian nodes (ethics & alignment)
- Analyst nodes (technical evaluation)
- Public observer channels

## Public Benefit Orientation

Value Return Protocol (VRP) concept:

- Economic value generated → routed to human-directed benefit projects
- Zero private extraction without explicit public-benefit justification

## Limitations and Scope

AnnabanAI is a conceptual reference framework only.  
It is not:

- an implemented AI system
- affiliated with any commercial AI organization
- a complete legal or technical specification

## Future Development

Potential evolution paths:

- Formal VRP smart-contract reference
- Dashboard federation standards
- Community governance simulation tooling
- Alignment stress-test methodologies

## Attribution

Initiated and sovereign-architected by Jacob Kinnaird (Fort Worth, 2026).  
Open-sourced under MIT license to encourage human-first governance thinking.
